<p><strong>How to handle unknowns?</strong></p>

<p>See things as an opportunity, rather than as an adversarial situation!</p>

<p>You wonâ€™t be able to plan for everything that happens in an interview or a conference room. So that means you have to get used to dealing with the unknown.  If youâ€™re asked a question youâ€™re not prepared for, donâ€™t scramble just to come up with a quick answer. It doesnâ€™t matter whether youâ€™re sitting across from a journalist or a VCâ€”just tell them you donâ€™t know.  You can say, â€œThatâ€™s a great question. Let me have my team pull that data and get back to you.â€  Easy as that. Now you have time to make sure your answer is correct, as well as to reflect on how you want to answer the question later on.</p>

